oda-data-set.name: service_details
oda-data-set.xml-property: WITH params AS ( SELECT ? AS cycle_log_id, ? AS account_id ), charges AS ( SELECT isc.invoice_service_charge_id, isc.invoice_service_bundle_id, isc.service_id, isc.order_charge_id, isc.charge_description, isc.from_date, isc.to_date, isc.quantity, isc.unit_rate, isc.total_price, om.format_product_circuit_id( isb.circuit_id, bc.product_cd ) AS circuit_id, order_nm as salesforce_order_id, --'SOF-'||substring(isb.circuit_id from '.{2}-.{3,4}-.{2,3}-(\d{5}).*') as salesforce_order_id, charge_type_cd, order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, bill_date, product, SPLIT_PART( change_order_id, '-', 1 ) AS order_number, order_type_cd FROM biller.invoice_service_bundles isb JOIN biller.invoice_service_charges isc USING (invoice_service_bundle_id) JOIN biller.cycle_log USING (cycle_log_id) JOIN om.order_charges USING (order_charge_id) JOIN om.orders USING (order_id) JOIN om.billing_components bc USING (billing_component_id) JOIN om.billing_component_types bct ON (bc.product_cd = bct.product_cd AND bc.billing_component_type_cd = bct.billing_component_type_cd) JOIN common.products p ON (bc.product_cd = p.product_cd) WHERE cycle_log_id = (SELECT cycle_log_id FROM params) AND isb.account_id = (SELECT account_id FROM params) --Filter out $0 NRC Charges AND (charge_type_cd = 'MR' OR total_price != 0) --Filter out mrc nrc does not apply when not zero AND (total_price != 0 OR (charge_type_cd = 'MR' AND bct.mrc_na IS FALSE)) AND sab_charge_type IS NULL ), a_locs as ( SELECT order_id, common.format_us_address(address1, address2, city, state_cd, zip, zip4) as address FROM om.order_addresses where order_id IN (select order_id from charges) and 'ALoc' = ANY(tags) and disabled > now() ), z_locs as ( SELECT order_id, common.format_us_address(address1, address2, city, state_cd, zip, zip4) as address FROM om.order_addresses where order_id IN (select order_id from charges) and 'ZLoc' = ANY(tags) and disabled > now() ), address_locs as ( SELECT order_id, common.format_us_address(address1, address2, city, state_cd, zip, zip4) as address FROM om.order_addresses where order_id IN (select order_id from charges) and tags = '{}' and disabled > now() ), colo_locs as ( SELECT order_id, location from om.product_co where order_id IN (select order_id from charges) and disabled > now() and nullif(location, 'Other') is not null ), -- Get the latest contract terms for an order that billed in this cycle latest_contract_terms AS ( SELECT DISTINCT ON (1) o.service_id, term_cd, term, contract_start_date :: DATE FROM biller.cycle_service_charges csc JOIN om.order_charges USING (order_charge_id) JOIN om.orders o USING (order_id) JOIN common.terms USING (term_cd) WHERE cycle_log_id = (SELECT cycle_log_id FROM params) ORDER BY 1 DESC, 2, 3 ), --Determine if they are a prorate prorate_logic AS ( SELECT *, CASE WHEN order_id != ( SELECT MAX(order_id) FROM om.orders WHERE service_id = charges.service_id GROUP BY service_id ) THEN TRUE WHEN (from_date != bill_date) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS is_prorate FROM charges ), with_disco_single_days AS ( SELECT invoice_service_charge_id, order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, charge_type_cd, order_number, circuit_id, salesforce_order_id, product, charge_description, from_date, to_date, CASE WHEN total_price > 0 OR total_price = 0 THEN (to_date - from_date) + 1 ELSE NULL END AS days_billed, CASE WHEN total_price < 0 THEN (to_date - from_date) + 1 ELSE NULL END AS days_refunded, total_price AS amt, order_type_cd, is_prorate, quantity, service_id FROM prorate_logic WHERE total_price != 0 OR is_prorate IS FALSE ), discos_summed AS ( SELECT dtc.order_id, dtc.customer_pon, dtc.billing_reference, dtc.charge_type_cd, dtc.order_number :: BIGINT, dtc.circuit_id, dtc.salesforce_order_id, dtc.product, dtc.charge_description, (dtc.from_date + INTERVAL '1 Day') :: DATE AS from_date, dtc.to_date, dtc.days_billed, dtc.days_refunded - 1 AS days_refunded, dtc.amt + dt.amt AS amt, dtc.quantity, dtc.invoice_service_charge_id AS invoice_service_charge_id_1, dt.invoice_service_charge_id AS invoice_service_charge_id_2, dt.service_id FROM with_disco_single_days dt JOIN with_disco_single_days dtc ON ( --Order id, circuit id AND charge description 100% match --Get the first refund row we could have multiple, just in case so we don't show the refund amt multiple times dtc.invoice_service_charge_id IN ( SELECT invoice_service_charge_id FROM with_disco_single_days dtc2 WHERE dt.order_number = dtc2.order_number AND dt.circuit_id = dtc2.circuit_id AND dt.charge_description = dtc2.charge_description AND dtc2.order_type_cd != 'DS' -- Date overlaps charge AND charge is not FROM the disco AND (dt.from_date, dt.to_date) OVERLAPS (dtc2.from_date, dtc2.to_date) AND days_refunded > 0 ) ) WHERE dt.order_type_cd = 'DS' ), all_charges AS ( SELECT ROW_NUMBER() OVER ( ORDER BY order_number, from_date, to_date, circuit_id, product, charge_description ) AS row_number, q.* FROM ( --Select the combined disco charges SELECT charge_type_cd, order_number, order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, circuit_id, salesforce_order_id, product, charge_description, from_date, to_date, days_billed, days_refunded, amt, quantity, service_id FROM discos_summed --Select all charges filter out the combined disco charges using subqueries UNION ALL SELECT charge_type_cd, order_number :: BIGINT, order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, circuit_id, salesforce_order_id, product, charge_description, from_date, to_date, days_billed, days_refunded, oda-data-set.name: late-aging

oda-data-set.name: service_charges_by_month
oda-data-set.xml-property: WITH params as ( SELECT ? as account_id, ? as cycle_log_id ), charges as ( SELECT isc.from_date, isc.to_date, total_price, opc.product_cd, billing_component_type_cd, case when order_type_cd='DS' then parent_order_id else order_id end as order_id, --split_part(change_order_id, '-', 1) as order_id, case when order_nm is null then order_id::text else order_nm end as salesforce_order_id, --'SOF-'||substring(circuit_id from '.{2}-.{3,4}-.{2,3}-(\d{5}).*') as salesforce_order_id, billing_reference, customer_pon, opc.charge_type_cd, om.format_product_circuit_id(isb.circuit_id, opc.product_cd) AS circuit_id, isb.circuit_id != om.format_product_circuit_id(isb.circuit_id, opc.product_cd) as is_product_charge FROM biller.invoice_service_bundles isb INNER JOIN biller.invoice_service_charges isc USING (invoice_service_bundle_id) INNER JOIN om.order_product_charges opc USING (order_charge_id) INNER JOIN om.billing_components USING (billing_component_id) INNER JOIN om.orders USING (order_id) where cycle_log_id = (select cycle_log_id from params) and isb.account_id = (select account_id from params) ), d_charges as ( SELECT DISTINCT from_date, to_date, circuit_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, salesforce_order_id, --'SOF-'||substring(circuit_id from '.{2}-.{3,4}-.{2,3}-(\d{5}).*') as salesforce_order_id, order_id, date_trunc('month', from_date) as billing_month, CASE WHEN is_product_charge IS TRUE THEN product_cd ELSE null END AS product_cd FROM charges c ), grouped_d as ( select min(from_date) as from_date, max(to_date) as to_date, circuit_id, product_cd, order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, salesforce_order_id, --'SOF-'||substring(circuit_id from '.{2}-.{3,4}-.{2,3}-(\d{5}).*') as salesforce_order_id, billing_month FROM d_charges GROUP BY circuit_id, order_id, billing_month, product_cd, customer_pon, billing_reference,salesforce_order_id ), charges_display as ( SELECT circuit_id, salesforce_order_id, --'SOF-'||substring(circuit_id from '.{2}-.{3,4}-.{2,3}-(\d{5}).*') as salesforce_order_id, customer_pon, billing_reference, order_id::bigint, billing_month, (select min(from_date) FROM d_charges d2 where date_trunc('month', c.from_date) = date_trunc('month', d2.from_date)) as min_from_date, (select max(to_date) FROM d_charges d3 where date_trunc('month', c.to_date) = date_trunc('month', d3.to_date)) as max_to_date, coalesce((SELECT sum(total_price) FROM charges c2 where c2.from_date BETWEEN c.from_date AND c.to_date AND c.order_id = c2.order_id and charge_type_cd = 'MR' and c2.salesforce_order_id=c.salesforce_order_id and (c.product_cd IS NULL or c.product_cd = c2.product_cd)), 0) as mrc, coalesce((SELECT sum(total_price) FROM charges c2 where c2.from_date BETWEEN c.from_date AND c.to_date AND c.order_id = c2.order_id and charge_type_cd = 'NR' and c2.salesforce_order_id=c.salesforce_order_id and (c.product_cd IS NULL or c.product_cd = c2.product_cd)), 0) as nrc from grouped_d c order by from_date, to_date, order_id::bigint ) SELECT *, (select count(*) > 1 FROM charges_display where order_id = cd.order_id and billing_month = cd.billing_month) as multiple_circuits FROM charges_display cd --WHERE ((select bill_date from biller.cycle_log where cycle_log_id = (select cycle_log_id from params)) BETWEEN min_from_date and max_to_date) or mrc > 0 or nrc > 0 order by billing_month, order_id::bigint

text.name: Invoice Instructions
text.text-property:
1. Account Summary. Provides an overview of the current activity on your account and your current account balance.

  2. Remittance Section. Please enter the amount paid and mail this section with your payment.

  3. Account Details. Displays your aged account balance as well as any late fees, account adjustments, work order charges, usage charges, and administrative fees that may have been applied to your account.

  4. Service Charge Overview. Provides a listing of totals of any Monthly Recurring Charges (MRC) and Non-Recurring Charges (NRC), grouped by Order Number and Circuit ID.

  5. Service Charge Details. Shows your charges grouped by services such as Private Line, Ethernet, or Dedicated Internet Access.

  6. Usage Overview (Optional). If your account has any usage charges, this section provides a summary of usage charges broken out by Call Type, Tax Type, and Duration.

  7. Usage Details (Optional). If your account has any usage charges, this section displays usage charge details by date and call type.

  8. Tax Overview. Provides an overview of all taxes charged for the current invoice
